%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20much%20should%20you%20tip%20on%20food%20delivery%3F%20Drivers%20say%20it%20should%20be%20based%20on%20distance%20and%20time%2C%20not%20just%20the%20total%20bill.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224096%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20door-dash%20delivery%20driver%20waits%20near%20a%20restaurant%20on%20December%2030%2C%202020%20in%20New%20York%20City.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b85e288a4e660019e3adf2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223072%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHow%20much%20should%20you%20tip%20for%20food%20delivery%3F%20Drivers%20said%20consider%20distance%20and%20time%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20catchall%20percentage.%3Cp%3EAlexi%20Rosenfeld%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDelivery%20drivers%20are%20weighing%20in%20on%20a%20contentious%20debate%20over%20what%20constitutes%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-to-tip-food-delivery-driver-doordash-ubereats-2023-7%5C%22%3Ea%20good%20tip.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESome%20drivers%20say%20a%20good%20tip%20is%20roughly%2015%25%20to%2020%25%20gratuity%20on%20the%20total%20cost%20of%20a%20delivery%20order.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOthers%20say%20percentage-based%20tips%20don't%20always%20account%20for%20the%20time%20and%20effort%20some%20deliveries%20take.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20recently%20asked%2010%20delivery%20drivers%20to%20weigh%20in%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcustomers-being-asked-to-tip-everywhere-theyre-sick-of-it-2023-3%5C%22%3Ehotly%20contested%20issue%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-to-tip-food-delivery-driver-doordash-ubereats-2023-7%5C%22%3EHow%20much%20should%20you%20tip%20on%20a%20%2420%20food%20delivery%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20stemmed%20from%20a%20recent%20incident%2C%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-doordash-delivery-worker-tipping-culture-america-2023-7%5C%22%3EDoorDash%20fired%20a%20driver%20who%20cursed%20at%20a%20woman%20for%20tipping%20%245%20on%20a%20%2420%20order%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drivers%20Insider%20interviewed%20generally%20agreed%20that%20the%20baseline%20for%20a%20good%20tip%20is%20between%2015%25%20to%2020%25%20of%20the%20total%20bill%20%E2%80%94%20including%20taxes%20and%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20publishing%20our%20story%2C%20however%2C%20several%20current%20and%20former%20drivers%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-uber-eats-grubhub-sue-new-york-city-minimum-wage-2023-7%5C%22%3EDoorDash%2C%20Grubhub%2C%20Uber%20Eats%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20delivery%20platforms%20emailed%20us%20saying%20the%20article%20missed%20a%20key%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPercentage-based%20tips%20don't%20always%20account%20for%20the%20time%20and%20effort%20it%20takes%20to%20deliver%20an%20order%2C%20drivers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EConsider%20delivery%20time%20and%20distance%20when%20tipping%2C%20drivers%20say%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20a%20%245%20tip%20on%20a%20%2420%20order%20is%20good%20(or%20bad)%20can%20depend%20on%20the%20circumstances%20of%20the%20delivery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELong%20routes%2C%20traffic%2C%20difficulty%20parking%2C%20and%20restaurant%20delays%20can%20all%20make%20that%20%245%20less%20valuable%2C%20drivers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20in%20mind%2C%20customers%20should%20consider%20boosting%20tips%20for%20longer%20delivery%20routes%2C%20they%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDashers%20like%20me%20who%20are%20trying%20to%20earn%20a%20minimum%20hourly%20do%20not%20select%20orders%20based%20on%20whether%20or%20not%20the%20tip%20is%20proportional%20to%20their%20total%20order%2C%26quot%3B%20Navi%20Vong%2C%20a%20delivery%20driver%20who%20works%20for%20both%20DoorDash%20and%20Uber%20Eats%2C%20told%20Insider%20by%20email.%20%26quot%3BInstead%2C%20we%20select%20orders%20based%20on%20distance%20to%20the%20customer%20and%20how%20much%20the%20total%20offer%20is.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20New%20York%20City%20%E2%80%94%20or%20at%20least%20the%20financial%20district%20of%20Manhattan%20where%20we%20conducted%20our%20initial%20driver%20survey%20%E2%80%94%20distances%20can%20be%20nominal.%20For%20example%2C%20we%20ordered%20coffee%20from%20a%20Starbucks%20that%20was%20roughly%20400%20feet%20from%20Insider's%20office.%20If%20you%20estimate%20an%20arbitrary%20base%20pay%20of%20%242%20and%20our%20tip%20of%20%242.50%2C%20drivers%20could%20earn%20around%20%244.50%20on%20an%20order%20that%20took%20maybe%2010%20minutes%20to%20complete.%20That%20could%20amount%20to%20%2427%20an%20hour%20if%20a%20driver%20could%20nab%20five%20other%20similar%20jobs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%20though%2C%20where%20the%20distance%20between%20a%20customer%20and%20a%20restaurant%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20miles%2C%20the%20calculus%20changes%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20for%20drivers%20paying%20for%20gas%20and%20vehicle%20wear-and-tear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCouriers%20use%20their%20own%20vehicles%2C%20complete%20with%20insurance%2C%20gas%2C%20and%20other%20maintenance%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20Vong%20wrote.%20In%20the%20Phoenix%20area%20where%20Vong%20works%2C%20earning%20less%20than%20roughly%20%2420%20per%20hour%20%26quot%3Bis%20not%20enough%20for%20the%20cost%20it%20takes%20to%20maintain%20the%20vehicle%20to%20deliver%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20drivers%20said%20they%20are%20constantly%20analyzing%C2%A0%20distance%2C%20travel%20times%2C%20and%20wait%20times%20in%20order%20to%20maximize%20their%20hourly%20earnings.%20Some%20have%20even%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-drivers-want-extra-tips-before-delivery-customers-complain-2023-5%5C%22%3Easking%20customers%20for%20higher%20tips%20before%20delivery.%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Though%20customers%20sometimes%20promise%20a%20big%20tip%2C%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-ceo-became-undercover-boss-used-tesla-surprised-rude-riders-2023-4%5C%22%3Ereduce%20it%20later%20in%20a%20practice%20called%20tip-baiting%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHeaven%20Leigh%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Arizona%2C%20told%20Insider%20she%20drives%20for%20DoorDash%20outside%20of%20her%20full-time%20job%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%20She%20often%20considers%20restaurants'%20speediness%20when%20weighing%20whether%20to%20accept%20a%20delivery%20offer%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20certain%20restaurants%20I%20decline%20every%20time%20because%20I%20know%20it%20will%20take%20too%20long%20for%20me%20to%20wait%20for%20the%20food%2C%20so%20if%20I%20end%20up%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20the%20drop%20off%20takes%20too%20long%20it%20can%20be%20devastating%20when%20I%20know%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffood-delivery-drivers-say-customers-dont-tip-enough-make-living-2023-4%5C%22%3Emy%20car%20payment%20is%20dependent%20on%20this%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20Leigh%20wrote%20by%20email.%20She%20said%20she%20maintains%20a%20personal%20goal%20of%20earning%20at%20least%20%241%20per%20mile.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20DoorDash%20said%2C%20however%2C%20that%20company%20data%20shows%20Dashers%20generally%20earn%20more%20during%20the%20course%20of%20their%20route%20when%20they%20accept%20more%20orders%20than%20when%20they%20%26quot%3Bcherry-pick%26quot%3B%20jobs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20also%20said%20it%20gives%20drivers%20the%20option%20to%20to%20choose%20between%20two%20payment%20options%3A%20%26quot%3Bearn%20by%20time%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bearn%20by%20offer.%26quot%3B%20The%20latter%20option%20takes%20into%20account%20factors%20like%20estimated%20duration%2C%20distance%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bdesirability%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20order%2C%20the%20company%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatrick%20Schoonover%2C%20a%20former%20DoorDash%20driver%2C%20said%20customers%20in%20general%20should%20think%20of%20deliveries%20as%20a%20service%20that%20is%20separate%20from%20their%20food%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20need%20to%20stop%20thinking%20about%20the%20total%20order%20on%20tipping%2C%20but%20actually%20how%20much%20it%20costs%20a%20driver%20to%20play%20the%20role%20of%20a%20personal%20(most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20exclusive)%20courier%20for%20their%20food%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Insider%20by%20email.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-should-you-tip-for-delivery-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690109101000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60566c1b1fcb5700186ee91d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-should-you-tip-for-delivery-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22What%20makes%20a%20good%20tip%3F%20Delivery%20drivers%20said%20a%20catchall%20percentage%20doesn't%20always%20account%20for%20the%20time%20and%20effort%20it%20takes%20to%20deliver%20orders.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22wgendron%40insider.com%20(Will%20Gendron%2CLakshmi%20Varanasi)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-should-you-tip-for-delivery-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22FOMO%2C%20YOLO%2C%20RINO%3A%20The%20quirkiest%20catchphrases%20explaining%20the%20surprising%20buoyancy%20of%20the%20stock%20market%20and%20economy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Traders%20work%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20New%20York%20Stock%20Exchange%20on%20May%2025%2C%202023%2C%20in%20New%20York%20City.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64709f933be3b50019f6f3de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETraders%20work%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20New%20York%20Stock%20Exchange%20on%20May%2025%2C%202023%2C%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3Cp%3ETIMOTHY%20A.%20CLARY%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EExperts%20have%20struggled%20to%20find%20textbook%20explanations%20for%20the%20surprising%20economic%20buoyancy%20and%20stock-market%20rally%20of%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMany%20commentators%20have%20instead%20turned%20to%20trendy%20catchphrases%20-%20such%20as%20FOMO%20and%20YOLO%20-%20to%20describe%20the%20behavior%20of%20investors%20and%20consumers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHere's%20a%20roundup%20of%20the%20quirkiest%20buzzwords%20used%20to%20comment%20on%20US%20equities%20and%20the%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20market%20experts%20have%20been%20at%20a%20loss%20to%20explain%20this%20year's%20surprisingly%20buoyant%20trend%20in%20US%20stocks%2C%20despite%20a%20slew%20of%20signals%20that%20the%20economy%20may%20be%20headed%20for%20a%20recession.%20Even%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20aggressive%20interest-rate%20increases%20and%20a%20bout%20of%20banking%20turmoil%20failed%20to%20rein%20the%20equity%20market's%20momentum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20a%20lack%20of%20classic%20textbook%20explanations%2C%20many%20commentators%20have%20turned%20to%20a%20bunch%20of%20informal%20acronyms%20to%20reason%20the%20market%20trends%20%E2%80%94%20FOMO%2C%20YOLO%2C%20RINO%20are%20some%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stock%20rally%20started%20early%20this%20year%20following%20the%20smashing%20debut%20of%20OpenAI's%20ChatGPT%2C%20which%20helped%20ignite%20a%20surge%20in%20investor%20excitement%20over%20tech%20shares.%20That%20helped%20boost%20the%20Nasdaq%20100%20by%20about%2040%25%20year-to-date%2C%20while%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20advanced%20about%2018%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20market%20ebullience%20isn't%20just%20down%20to%20AI%20hype.%20Investors%20have%20been%20driven%20by%20a%20mix%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fai-tech-stocks-markets-investing-fomo-retail-average-investors-nvidia-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFOMO%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20fear%20of%20missing%20out%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20a%20sense%20of%20relief%20that%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2F10-reasons-recession-wall-street-predicted-to-death-never-happened-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emuch-predicted%20recession%20never%20arrived%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20US%20economy%20appears%20to%20be%20in%20surprisingly%20good%20shape.%20And%20it's%20down%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Feconomy-outlook-yolo-consumers-summer-spending-jobs-report-rate-hikes-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYOLO%20consumers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20Wharton%20professor%20Jeremy%20Siegel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20of%20the%20in-vogue%20catchwords%20that%20have%20been%20widely%20used%20to%20describe%20and%20explain%20market%20trends%20in%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EFOMO%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EChatGPT's%20overnight%20success%20sent%20investors%20rushing%20to%20buy%20into%20companies%20perceived%20as%20being%20well%20positioned%20to%20benefit%20from%20the%20AI%20revolution.%20The%20buying%20frenzy%20in%20turn%20spurred%20even%20traders%20who%20were%20on%20the%20sidelines%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-outlook-fed-rates-jeremy-siegel-recession-housing-economy-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejump%20on%20the%20AI%20train%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20giving%20rise%20to%20a%20fear-of-missing-out%20rally.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20momentum%20and%20fear%20of%20missing%20out%20on%20gains%20can%20take%20the%20market%20higher%20over%20the%20short%20run%2C%26quot%3B%20Siegel%20said%20in%20a%20weekly%20WisdomTree%20commentary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20it%20can%20last%20is%20a%20key%20question.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20long%20can%20such%20optimism%20or%20exuberance%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BAI%20bandwagon%26quot%3B%20continue%3F%20If%20we%20argue%20that%20it%20is%20more%20heavily%20driven%20by%20the%20liquidity%20factor%20it%20implies%20that%20such%20FOMO%20behaviour%20can%20morph%20into%20a%20mania%20that%20can%20be%20severely%20out%20of%20synch%20with%20economic%20realities%20akin%20to%20the%20prior%20boom-bust%20cycles%20of%20similar%20high%20technology%20advancement%20narratives%2C%26quot%3B%20OANDA%20analyst%20Kelvin%20Wong%20wrote%20in%20a%20blog.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ERINO%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMove%20over%2C%20bulls%20and%20bears.%20A%20new%20variety%20of%20animal%20spirit%20may%20be%20driving%20the%20market%20now.%20According%20to%20a%20new%20acronym%20coined%20by%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20what%20we%20have%20in%20place%20is%20a%20RINO%20rally.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDeveloped%20economies%20continue%20to%20surprise%20positively.%20Inflation%20is%20cooling%20down%20and%20a%20soft%20landing%20now%20looks%20like%20a%20plausible%20outcome.%20This%20has%20led%20to%20a%20new%20acronym%20(courtesy%20of%20Goldman)%3A%20the%20%26quot%3BRecession%20In%20Name%20Only%26quot%3B%20(R.I.N.O)%2C%26quot%3B%20analysts%20at%20the%20boutique%20Swiss%20bank%20SYZ%20wrote%20in%20a%20note.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20appears%20to%20suggest%20that%20the%20much-expected%20US%20recession%20has%20remained%20just%20a%20hypothesis%20and%20not%20a%20reality%2C%20given%20how%20resilient%20the%20economy%20has%20shown%20itself%20to%20be.%20And%20that's%20a%20cheerful%20enough%20situation%20for%20traders%20to%20pile%2