ck.%20The%20Great%20Resignation%20was%20supposed%20to%20help%20them%20gain%20more%20power%2C%20money%2C%20and%20benefits%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwrong-great-resignation-recession-means-workers-powerless-despite-labor-shortage-2022-7%5C%22%3Ethat%20hasn't%20worked%20out%20as%20planned%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Now%2C%20as%20the%20labor%20market%20cools%2C%20conditions%20are%20ripe%20for%20grumpy%20stayers%20to%20get%20even%20grumpier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20pretty%20much%20stuck%20here%20doing%20this%20work%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Gonzalez%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20talking%20to%20an%20acquaintance%20of%20mine%20who's%20a%20recruiter%2C%20and%20he's%20telling%20me%20summer%20is%20the%20slow%20time.%20There%20are%20no%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFiltered%20out%20from%20jobs%20that%20might%20make%20them%20happy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGrumpy%20stayers%20come%20in%20many%20forms.%20Some%2C%20like%20Gonzalez%2C%20shuffled%20into%20jobs%20that%20weren't%20as%20good%20a%20fit%20as%20they'd%20hoped.%20Others%2C%20like%20Elizabeth%2C%20a%20barista%20in%20Massachusetts%2C%20have%20found%20themselves%20spinning%20in%20the%20same%20role%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElizabeth%20has%20been%20at%20her%20company%20for%2018%20years.%20(Insider%20knows%20her%20last%20name%20and%20employer%20but%20is%20withholding%20them%20for%20privacy%20reasons.)%20She%20said%20she'd%20been%20staying%20at%20her%20role%20out%20of%20inertia.%20She's%20been%20job%20hunting%20for%20a%20year%2C%20even%20for%20just%20a%20second%20part-time%20job%2C%20but%20to%20no%20avail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can't%20find%20anything%20that%20pays%20more%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20what%20I'm%20making%20%E2%80%94%20that%20doesn't%20require%20me%20to%20be%20certified%20or%20have%20a%20degree%20in%20something%20that%20I%20don't%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%20she%20found%20herself%20tipping%20over%20the%20grumpy%20edge.%20She%20figured%20she'd%20never%20be%20able%20to%20get%20a%20higher-paying%20position%20without%20spending%20time%20in%20a%20management%20role%2C%20so%20when%20an%20opportunity%20to%20move%20into%20a%20management%20position%20arose%2C%20she%20applied.%20But%20after%20she%20got%20passed%20over%20for%20the%20role%2C%20she%20started%20having%20panic%20attacks%20at%20work%2C%20she%20said.%20She%20added%20that%20at%20one%20point%20she%20almost%20walked%20out%20but%20then%20found%20herself%20sitting%20on%20the%20floor%20and%20crying%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20she's%20on%20leave%20from%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20both%20causing%20and%20exacerbating%20a%20lot%20of%20my%20problems%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20this%20job%20is%20how%20I%20get%20paid%20leave%20and%20mental-health%20care%20and%20all%20that%20good%20stuff.%20That's%20part%20of%20that%20golden-handcuffs%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElizabeth%20is%20far%20from%20the%20only%20person%20facing%20this%20situation.%20Erica%20Groshen%2C%20a%20senior%20economics%20advisor%20at%20Cornell%20University's%20School%20of%20Industrial%20and%20Labor%20Relations%2C%20said%20many%20people%20who%20didn't%20change%20jobs%20have%20%26quot%3Bseen%20a%20lot%20of%20their%20more-mobile%20colleagues%20go%20off%20and%20get%20likely%20to%20be%20higher%20paid%20or%20higher%20benefit%2C%20or%20some%20otherwise%20more%20attractive%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20grumpy%20stayers%20might%20be%20feeling%20left%20behind%2C%20with%20salaries%20lagging%20behind%20those%20of%20their%20peers%20who've%20departed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies'%20actions%20are%20also%20helping%20drive%20the%20trend.%20Groshen%20said%20specific%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-paying-jobs-without-degrees-obama-shortage-biden-student-debt-2023-3%5C%22%3Edegree%20or%20credential%20requirements%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20keeping%20capable%20workers%20from%20getting%20jobs%2C%20even%20at%