20that%20his%20mortgage%20went%20up%20%241%2C000%20a%20month.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFEMA%20placed%20his%20home%20in%20a%20flood%20zone%2C%20and%20his%20bank%20bought%20him%20flood%20insurance%20without%20telling%20him.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECollins%20now%20has%20to%20pay%20%248%2C000%20more%20a%20year%20than%20he%20originally%20budgeted%20for.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Florida%20resident%20and%20former%20baseball%20player%20Danny%20Collins%2C%20whose%20mortgage%20on%20a%20%24400%2C000%2C%20four-bedroom%20home%20jumped%20%241%2C000%20per%20month%20with%20no%20warning%20after%20FEMA%20redrew%20its%20flood%20zone%20maps%2C%20placing%20his%20home%20in%20a%20flood%20zone.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20and%20I%20live%20in%20Hobe%20Sound%2C%20Florida.%20We're%20lifelong%20Florida%20residents%20and%20found%20a%20good%20home%20that%20fit%20all%20our%20needs%20two%20years%20ago.%20It's%20four%20bedrooms%2C%20two%20bathrooms%2C%20and%201%2C700%20square%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERent%20around%20here%20now%20is%20crazy%20and%20in%20looking%20for%20a%20house%20we%20were%20mostly%20concerned%20about%20the%20monthly%20rate.%20Our%20mortgage%20payment%20was%20initially%20%242%2C000.%20It%20was%20in%20our%20budget%20and%20we%20were%20thrilled%20to%20be%20homeowners.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20we're%20on%20the%20coast%2C%20we%20initially%20weren't%20in%20a%20flood%20zone.%20But%20FEMA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wpbf.com%2Farticle%2Ffema-hikes-flood-insurance-rates-along-treasure-coast%2F39614897%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eredid%20all%20the%20flood%20maps%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022%20and%20our%20home%20was%20placed%20in%20one.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20surprised%20because%20we're%20just%20east%20of%20US-1%20and%20that's%20a%20good%20three%20miles%20from%20the%20ocean%2C%20so%20flooding%20wasn't%20a%20concern%20of%20mine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20shocked%20when%20we%20got%20the%20new%20mortgage%20bill%20and%20it%20was%20%243%2C100.%20I%20had%20no%20idea%2C%20nobody%20contacted%20us%20beforehand.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20was%20I%20supposed%20to%20plan%20for%20this%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bank%20wasn't%20very%20helpful.%20I%20was%20really%20upset%20because%20there%20was%20no%20communication.%20They%20just%20said%20that%20there%20was%20flood%20insurance%20that%20we%20had%20to%20have%2C%20and%20they%20had%20bought%20it%20for%20us.%20We%20were%20like%2C%20'Why%20didn't%20anybody%20contact%20us%20and%20let%20us%20know%3F'%20Instead%20they%20just%20take%20one%20out%20for%20you%20and%20it%20was%20the%20most%20expensive%20one%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ended%20up%20shopping%20for%20insurance%20companies%20and%20got%20it%20back%20down%20to%20%242%2C776.%20We%20paid%20one%20month%20of%20%243%2C100%20before%20getting%20it%20back%20down.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20everybody%20I've%20spoken%20to%20in%20the%20neighborhood%2C%20their%20insurance%20has%20gone%20up.%20I%20haven't%20met%20a%20person%20yet%20who%20hasn't%20experienced%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20really%20plan%20for%20this.%20We%20were%20budgeting%20for%20a%20fixed%20rate%20of%20what%20we%20thought%20our%20mortgage%20was%20going%20to%20be.%20I'm%20fortunate%20that%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20do%20well%20enough%20to%20be%20able%20to%20cover%20it%20but%20that's%20an%20over%20%24700%20a%20month%20difference.%20It's%20almost%20an%20%248%2C000%20per%20year%20increase%20in%20fees%2C%20which%20makes%20a%20big%20difference.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20a%20daunting%20future%20for%20my%20home%20state%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20really%20frustrating%20because%20it's%20not%20ever%20talked%20about.%20These%20are%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-insurers-will-shape-where-people-live-climate-change-2023-7%5C%22%3Eissues%20that%20ar