ted%20past%20100%20million%20users%3C%2Fa%3E%20less%20than%20a%20week%20after%20it%20went%20live.%20The%20explosive%20start%20from%20Mark%20Zuckerberg's%20latest%20brainchild%20made%20it%20the%20fastest-growing%20app%20in%20history%20and%20took%20a%20significant%20bite%20out%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F07%2F10%2Ftwitter-traffic-is-nosediving-as-metas-threads-hits-100-million-users.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETwitter's%20traffic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20the%20tracking%20company%20Cloudflare.%20The%20app%20has%20since%20been%20hailed%20as%20the%20Twitter%20replacement%20people%20have%20been%20clamoring%20for%20since%20Elon%20Musk's%20takeover%20%E2%80%94%20and%20bungling%20%E2%80%94%20of%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Threads%20does%20look%20eerily%20similar%20to%20Twitter%2C%20there%20are%20critical%20differences.%20The%20search%20experience%20is%20limited%20to%20finding%20accounts%2C%20with%20no%20ability%20to%20find%20people's%20posts%20or%20search%20by%20topic.%20There%20is%20no%20trending%20page%2C%20making%20it%20impossible%20to%20see%20what%20issues%20are%20dominating%20the%20discourse.%20The%20notifications%20are%20also%20a%20mess%2C%20there%20are%20no%20direct%20messages%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20option%20to%20see%20posts%20from%20only%20people%20you%20follow.%20Adam%20Mosseri%2C%20Instagram's%20head%2C%20says%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fca.finance.yahoo.com%2Fnews%2Fthreads-working-bunch-features-help-111756882.html%3Fguccounter%3D1%26guce_referrer%3DaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS8%26guce_referrer_sig%3DAQAAAGSS7fIcsdb-PZbrAvVt2Msj8el63vHpJQLkJ0it6dlfccrtMcNfcM6dWvmKYeu8iUGMUZlfb0mA-h-iPAAmeoHnv51zzeB7j8XZ-m1uVNVu98xFt7-Zu078vSjFzaai02eq4oOd_ov0BMlVUCBl8UHWkrWHBU_bNjzyh6x57kBm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20of%20those%20features%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20in%20the%20works%2C%20but%20even%20as%20the%20app%20evolves%2C%20it's%20becoming%20clear%20that%20it%20will%20never%20truly%20replace%20Twitter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20Meta%20isn't%20trying%20to%20fill%20the%20shoes%20of%20its%20competitor.%20While%20Twitter%20became%20popular%20as%20a%20place%20to%20stay%20informed%20and%20get%20access%20to%20critical%20information%2C%20Meta%20wants%20Threads%20to%20be%20a%20hangout%20space%20for%20lifestyle%20brands%20and%20influencers.%20Instead%20of%20a%20newsstand%2C%20Meta%20is%20building%20a%20new%20wing%20of%20its%20multiplatform%20mall.%20That%20might%20sound%20great%20to%20advertisers%2C%20but%20it's%20hard%20to%20imagine%20people%20will%20want%20to%20be%20confined%20to%20the%20vapid%20topics%20that%20do%20best%20on%20Instagram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Twitter%20became%20popular%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETwitter%20was%20never%20the%20biggest%20social-media%20platform%2C%20and%20the%20company%20was%20pretty%20bad%20at%20making%20money.%20But%20it%20managed%20to%20leverage%20its%20unique%20experience%20in%20such%20a%20way%20that%20it%20became%20a%20major%20part%20of%20news%20and%20current%20affairs%20throughout%20the%202010s.%20Politicians%2C%20journalists%2C%20and%20other%20newsmakers%20flocked%20to%20the%20platform%2C%20providing%20unprecedented%20insight%20into%20their%20influential%20roles%2C%20while%20giving%20them%20a%20more%20direct%20connection%20to%20regular%20people%2C%20and%20vice%20versa.%20Some%20high-profile%20users%2C%20such%20as%20President%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20became%20almost%20unavoidable%20%E2%80%94%20his%20tweets%20shaped%20news%20cycles%20and%20public%20policy.%20And%20when%20big%20events%20happened%20around%20the%20world%20or%20locally%2C%20Twitter%20was%20the%20first%20place%20to%20turn%20to%20for%20real-time%20updates%20from%20reporters%2C%20public%20agencies%2C%20and%20average%20people%20documenting%20events%20for%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20Twitter's%20magic%3A%20While%20there%20were%20plenty%20of%20influential%20people%20on%20the%20platform%2C%20there%20were%20far%20more%20regular%20users%20sharing%20whatever%20came%20to%20their%20minds%2C%20spouting%20off%20about%20topics%20they%20were%20passionate%20about%20and%20getting%20into%20discussions%20(or%20fiery%20arguments)%20with%20one%20another.%20The%20platform%20gave%20regular%20people%20a%20degree%20of%20collective%20power.%20If%20someone%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20an%20airline%2C%20a%20celebrity%2C%20or%20just%20some%20random%20person%20%E2%80%94%20said%20or%20did%20the%20wrong%20thing%2C%20users%20could%20band%20together%20and%20make%20the%20offender%20address%20the%20issue.%20Twitter%20allowed%20people%20to%20both%20know%20when%20their%20train%20was%20late%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-killed-twitter-irrelevant-meta-threads-debt-mark-zuckerberg-2023-7%5C%22%3Eyell%20at%20the%20train%20service%20about%20it%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20made%20it%20both%20useful%20and%20somewhat%20addictive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThe%20platform%20gave%20regular%20people%20a%20degree%20of%20collective%20power.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EMonetizing%20the%20chaotic%20stream%20of%20consciousness%20was%20always%20difficult%20for%20Twitter.%20It%20was%20estimated%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Ftechnology%2F2023%2Fjan%2F18%2Ftwitter-revenue-drop-advertising-squeeze-elon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E90%25%20of%20its%20revenue%3C%2Fa%3E%20came%20from%20advertising%20in%202021%2C%20but%20even%20then%2C%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F04%2F28%2Ftechnology%2Ftwitter-first-quarter-earnings-elon-musk.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebarely%20enough%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20cover%20its%20costs.%20These%20problems%20could%20have%20been%20addressed%20by%20a%20new%20leader%20with%20a%20clear%20vision%20to%20shake%20up%20the%20business.%20Instead%2C%20Twitter%20got%20a%20chaos%20agent%3A%20Musk.%20Instead%20of%20drilling%20down%20on%20ways%20to%20boost%20what%20made%20Twitter%20special%2C%20he%20laid%20off%20most%20of%20the%20staff%2C%20changed%20up%20how%20the%20platform%20worked%2C%20and%20inspired%20an%20exodus%20of%20advertisers.%20As%20the%20meltdown%20has%20gotten%20worse%2C%20the%20race%20to%20absorb%20Twitter's%20disaffected%20user%20base%20%E2%80%94%20and%20advertisers%20%E2%80%94%20has%20heated%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEnter%3A%20Threads%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20Threads%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.threads.net%2F%40mosseri%2Fpost%2FCuZ3LjhNl0m%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Mosseri%20said%20that%20the%20company's%20goal%20%26quot%3Bisn't%20to%20replace%20Twitter%26quot%3B%20but%20%26quot%3Bto%20create%20a%20public%20square%20for%20communities%20on%20Instagram%20that%20never%20really%20embraced%20Twitter%20and%20for%20communities%20on%20Twitter%20(and%20other%20platforms)%20that%20are%20interested%20in%20a%20less%20angry%20place%20for%20conversations.%26quot%3B%20In%20other%20words%2C%20Threads%20isn't%20targeting%20the%20entire%20Twitter%20user%20base%2C%20just%20a%20segment%20of%20it.%20In%20particular%2C%20Mosseri%20said%20that%20Meta%20wanted%20to%20welcome%20people%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.threads.net%2F%40mosseri%2Fpost%2FCuZ6opKtHva%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterested%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%26quot%3Bsports%2C%20music%2C%20fashion%2C%20beauty%2C%20entertainment%2C%20etc.%26quot%3B%20who%20want%20to%20have%20%26quot%3Ba%20vibrant%20platform%20without%20needing%20to%20get%20into%20politics%20or%20hard%20news.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20some%20level%2C%20Threads'%20aversion%20to%20Twitter's%20free-flowing%20conversation%20makes%20sense%20%E2%80%94%20discourse%20on%20Twitter%20can%20get%20pretty%20toxic.%20But%20before%20Musk%20took%20over%2C%20the%20platform%20was%20trying%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20the%20worst%20of%20it.%20Now%2C%20Musk%20has%20allowed%20a%20large%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmashable.com%2Farticle%2Felon-musk-reinstated-banned-twitter-accounts-list%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20barred%20right-wing%20extremists%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20return%20to%20the%20platform.%20And%20Musk's%20content-moderation%20policies%20and%20his%20own%20frequent%20boosting%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2Ftechnology%2F2023%2F5%2F20%2F23730607%2Felon-musk-conspiracy-twitter-texas-shooting-bellingcat-taylor-lorenz-psyops%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econspiracy%20theories%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenation.com%2Farticle%2Fsociety%2Felon-musk-transphobia-twitter%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanti-trans%20posts%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20incensed%20many%20users%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.semafor.com%2Farticle%2F04%2F09%2F2023%2Felon-musks-ad-problems%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escaring%20off%20advertisers%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20has%20had%20its%20own%20problems%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebooks-local-partners-say-hate-speech-stays-on-the-platform-2023-4%5C%22%3Ehate%20speech%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Facebook%20and%20continues%20to%20be%20under%20scrutiny%20for%20the%20harm%20caused%20by%20its%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnesty.org%2Fen%2Flatest%2Fnews%2F2022%2F09%2Fmyanmar-facebooks-systems-promoted-violence-against-rohingya-meta-owes-reparations-new-report%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eineffective%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmetas-moderation-is-failing-and-people-are-getting-killed-2023-6%5C%22%3Econtent%20moderation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20Meta's%20solution%20to%20toxic%20debate%2C%20it%20seems%2C%20is%20to%20shut%20it%20off%20any%20debate%20at%20all.%20This%20isn't%20a%20new%20idea%20for%20the%20company%3A%20Last%20year%2C%20Meta%20changed%20the%20name%20of%20Facebook's%20main%20timeline%20from%20%26quot%3BNews%20Feed%26quot%3B%20to%20simply%20%26quot%3BFeed%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20was%20partially%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cjr.org%2Fthe_media_today%2Fwill-facebook-changes-leave-news-media-out-in-the-cold.php%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexplained%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bde-emphasizing%20its%20investment%20in%20news%20content%26quot%3B%20and%20reducing%20the%20resources%20it%20invested%20in%20its%20news%20products.%20In%202021%2C%20it%20briefly%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Fnews%2F2021-02-18%2Ffacebook-to-restrict-sharing-or-viewing-news-in-australia%2F13166208%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epulled%20news%20in%20Australia%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20government%20began%20to%20force%20Google%20and%20Facebook%20to%20compensate%20local%20media.%20And%20it's%20now%20threatening%20to%20do%20the%20same%20in%20response%20to%20similar%20plans%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fonline-news-act-meta-facebook-1.6885634%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECanada%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F05%2F31%2Ftech%2Fmeta-threatens-to-pull-california-news%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECalifornia%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20message%20from%20Meta%20is%3A%20News%20content%20isn't%20as%20lucrative%20as%20it%20once%20was%2C%20or%20it%20just%20isn't%20worth%20the%20trade-offs.%20Ultimately%2C%20advertisers%20want%20to%20stay%20away%20from%20controversy%2C%20especially%20at%20a%20moment%20when%20almost%20anything%20can%20become%20a%20culture-war%20issue.%20And%20after%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmetaverse-dead-obituary-facebook-mark-zuckerberg-tech-fad-ai-chatgpt-2023-5%5C%22%3Emetaverse%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Meta%20is%20looking%20for%20its%20next%20cash%20cow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECreating%20a%20sanitized%20space%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201996%2C%20Jennifer%20S.%20Light%2C%20a%20technology%20historian%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fpdf%2F10.1068%2Fd140127%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompared%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20growth%20of%20commercial%20online%20communities%20to%20the%20shopping%20malls%20that%20sprung%20up%20across%20the%20US%20through%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%2020th%20century.%20Shopping%20malls%20were%20an%20attempt%20to%20provide%20a%20downtown%2C%20Main%20Street-style%20space%20for%20people%20who%20had%20fled%20to%20the%20suburbs.%20But%20since%20malls%20were%20privately%20owned%20spaces%20geared%20toward%20persuading%20customers%20to%20spend%20their%20cash%2C%20they%20weren't%20very%20welcoming%20to%20people%20who%20were%20not%20deemed%20ideal%20customers%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20people%20of%20color%20and%20homeless%20people.%20Even%20with%20our%20nostalgia-tinted%20view%20of%20these%20dying%20spaces%2C%20it's%20safe%20to%20say%20that%20malls%20are%20not%20the%20ideal%20community%20space.%20They%20weren't%20designed%20for%20people%3B%20they%20were%20designed%20to%20make%20money%20for%20the%20businesses%20inside%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThey%20weren't%20designed%20for%20people%3B%20they%20were%20designed%20to%20make%20money%20for%20the%20businesses%20inside%20them.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20web%20took%20off%20in%20the%20'90s%2C%20it%20was%20seen%20initially%20as%20a%20public%20space%20where%20people%20from%20all%20over%20the%20world%20would%20be%20able%20to%20come%20together%20and%20interact.%20Despite%20the%20early%20excitement%2C%20Light%20wrote%2C%20the%20rush%20to%20make%20money%20from%20the%20new%20technology%20meant%20that%20the%20web%20was%20quickly%20commodified%20like%20a%20shopping%20mall.%20As%20advertising%20became%20one%20of%20the%20central%20business%20models%20of%20the%20web%2C%20platforms%20were%20incentivized%20to%20limit%20what%20people%20could%20or%20couldn't%20do%20on%20them%20to%20make%20them%20more%20appealing%20spaces%20for%20advertisers%20to%20spend%20their%20dollars.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20this%20had%20a%20valuable%20moderating%20effect.%20Major%20companies%20don't%20want%20their%20ads%20to%20be%20placed%20alongside%20explicit%20material%2C%20hate%20speech%2C%20or%20violent%20imagery%2C%20so%20if%20platforms%20can't%20moderate%20these%20types%20of%20content%2C%20the%20business%20side%20will%20suffer.%20The%20flip%20side%20of%20this%20desire%20for%20clean%20spaces%20is%20that%20brands%20also%20don't%20want%20to%20put%20up%20with%20debates%20on%20sensitive%20political%20issues%2C%20conversations%20that%20expose%20their%20bad%20behavior%2C%20or%20even%20nude%20images%2C%20which%20have%20long%20been%20banned%20on%20Meta's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftechcrunch.com%2F2023%2F07%2F06%2Fyou-cant-post-ass-threads-is-doomed-meta-instagram-twitter%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplatforms%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20push%20to%20oversanitize%20and%20limit%20conversations%20to%20benign%2C%20lowest-common-denominator%20discussion%20turned%20the%20internet%20from%20a%20common%2C%20public%20market%20where%20everyone%20could%20hang%20out%20on%20equal%20footing%20into%20a%20commodified%2C%20poorly%20lit%20mall%20designed%20to%20cater%20to%20people%20who%20had%20the%20most%20to%20spend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThreads%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20the%20future%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20balancing%20act%20between%20providing%20a%20place%20for%20free%20expression%20and%20catering%20to%20advertisers%20is%20at%20the%20core%20of%20the%20Threads-Twitter%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Twitter%20had%20long%20been%20used%20for%20informative%20purposes%2C%20it%20was%20also%20a%20place%20where%20people%20could%20post%20fairly%20freely%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20occasionally%20caused%20some%20problems.%20There%20was%20always%20a%20tension%20about%20how%20much%20to%20moderate%20content%2C%20not%20just%20by%20users%20who%20wanted%20hate%20speech%20cleaned%20up%20but%20also%20by%20advertisers%20who%20wanted%20less%20risk%20to%20their%20brands.%20Instead%20of%20solving%20these%20issues%20while%20preserving%20what%20made%20it%20unique%2C%20Musk%20has%20pushed%20Twitter%20further%20into%20the%20free-for-all%20direction.%20Musk%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2022-04-05%2Felon-musk-opined-about-buying-twitter-after-babylon-bee-ban%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edirectly%20cited%3C%2Fa%3E%20attempts%20to%20increase%20moderation%20as%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20he%20chose%20to%20acquire%20the%20company%20and%20remake%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bfree%20speech%26quot%3B%20platform.%20But%2C%20as%20I%20already%20mentioned%2C%20that%20isn't%20going%20well%20for%20the%20business%20side%20of%20things.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20advertisers%20have%20fled%20Twitter%20in%20response%20to%20Musk's%20changes%2C%20Meta%20is%20learning%20from%20Musk's%20mistakes%20and%20trying%20to%20create%20the%20shopping-mall-ified%2C%20brand-friendly%20version%20of%20Twitter%20that%20the%20bird%20site%20could%20never%20succeed%20at%20turning%20itself%20into.%20Threads%20aims%20to%20build%20on%20the%20success%20of%20Instagram%2C%20which%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fjohnbbrandon%2F2023%2F06%2F24%2Finstagram-is-outpacing-tiktok-for-user-growth-heres-why%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethriving%3C%2Fa%3E%20amid%20Facebook's%20decline.%20Instagram's%20visual%20nature%20and%20strict%20content%20moderation%20make%20it%20great%20for%20advertising%2C%20and%20now%20Threads%20will%20provide%20those%20same%20brands%20and%20creators%20an%20additional%20space%20to%20promote%20their%20products.%20This%20is%20already%20clear%20in%20how%20Threads%20prioritizes%20users%3A%20Influencers%20and%20celebrities%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2023%2F7%2F6%2F23785588%2Fmeta-instagram-threads-celebrities-brands%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egot%20early%20access%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20app%20and%20have%20been%20relentlessly%20promoted%20by%20its%20algorithm.%20To%20jump-start%20engagement%2C%20these%20accounts%20started%20by%20asking%20their%20followers%20questions%20like%20their%20favorite%20color%20or%20whether%20they%20liked%20cookies%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that's%20not%20the%20level%20of%20discussion%20that%20will%20keep%20people%20engaged%20for%20very%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20say%20exactly%20how%20successful%20Threads%20will%20be.%20Some%20analysts%20are%20estimating%20it%20could%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-07-10%2Fmeta-s-threads-to-earn-8-billion-annual-revenue-by-2025-analyst-says%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadd%20%248%20billion%20to%20Meta's%20annual%20revenue%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%202025.%20But%20after%20the%20rush%20of%20initial%20sign-ups%2C%20tracking%20firms%20are%20already%20finding%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Ftech%2Ftech-news%2Fmeta-threads-engagement-dropped-red-hot-debut-tracking-firms-say-rcna94256%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esignificant%20drop%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20user%20engagement.%20Ultimately%2C%20how%20Threads%20does%20will%20be%20determined%20by%20whether%20users%20actually%20want%20a%20Twitter-like%20platform%20that%20puts%20vapid%20consumption%20above%20substantive%2C%20useful%2C%20and%20occasionally%20heated%20discussion.%20If%20Threads%20does%20succeed%2C%20it%20won't%20be%20the%20Twitter%20replacement%20people%20are%20hoping%20for.%20In%20its%20bid%20for%20a%20cash-cow%20app%2C%20Threads%20is%20foregoing%20everything%20that%20made%20Twitter%20special%20%E2%80%94%20no%20political%20debate%2C%20no%20train%20updates%2C%20no%20crowdsourcing%20breaking%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20will%20there%20ever%20be%20another%20Twitter%3F%20As%20its%20disintegration%20has%20continued%2C%20no%20app%20has%20succeeded%20in%20taking%20its%20place.%20Perhaps%20that's%20because%20Twitter%20is%20a%20relic%20of%20a%20waning%20era%20in%20online%20communication%2C%20where%20trading%20data%20for%20access%20may%20not%20be%20enough%20anymore.%20In%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Frising-interest-rates-might-herald-the-end-of-the-open-internet%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20moment%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20platforms%20are%20being%20forced%20to%20prove%20their%20business%20bona%20fides%20much%20quicker%2C%20an%20online%20mall%20may%20be%20the%20most%20realistic%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fparis-marx%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fparis-marx%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1689864404128000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3to2J7cACDYOwjd4Ib5ype%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EParis%20Marx%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20tech%20writer%20and%20host%20of%20the%20Tech%20Won't%20Save%20Us%20podcast.%20He%20also%20writes%20the%20Disconnect%20newsletter%20and%20is%20the%20author%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.versobooks.com%2Fbooks%2F3995-road-to-nowhere%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.go