%20poems%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98Postcard%20from%20Kashmir%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98In%20Arabic%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98The%20Last%20Saffron%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20and%20Peer%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ECurfewed%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ENight%3C%2Fem%3E%20were%20taught%20in%20the%20third%20semester%20of%20the%20Masters%20of%20Arts%20(English)%20course%20at%20the%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20works%20will%20no%20longer%20be%20part%20of%20the%20curriculum%20from%20this%20year%20onwards%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20source%20at%20the%20university%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20decision%20was%20conveyed%20%E2%80%9Corally%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Crelevant%20authorities%20after%20consultations%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20Vice-Chancellor%E2%80%99s%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20university%20has%20also%20removed%20the%20syllabus%20of%20the%20two-year%20masters%20programme%20from%20its%20website.%20Sources%20said%20that%20the%20syllabus%20will%20become%20accessible%20%E2%80%9Conce%20it%20has%20been%20updated.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20deletions%2C%20Professor%20Nilofer%20Khan%2C%20UoK%20Vice-Chancellor%2C%20said%20that%20she%20was%20%E2%80%9Cin%20a%20meeting%E2%80%9D%20and%20promised%20to%20get%20back.%20She%2C%20however%2C%20didn%E2%80%99t%20answer%20phone%20calls%20made%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20decision%20to%20discontinue%20Shahid%E2%80%99s%20two%20poems%2C%20%E2%80%98I%20see%20Kashmir%20from%20New%20Delhi%20at%20Midnight%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Call%20me%20Ishmael%20Tonight%2C%E2%80%99%20was%20taken%20by%20the%20Cluster%20University%20Srinagar%20(CUS)%2C%20officials%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98I%20see%20Kashmir%20from%20New%20Delhi%20at%20Midnight%E2%80%99%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20iconic%20explorations%20of%20the%20struggles%20faced%20by%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir%20since%20armed%20insurgency%20broke%20out%20in%20the%20early%20nineties.%20The%20poem%20touches%20on%20issues%20of%20torture%2C%20%E2%80%98bullet-torn%E2%80%99%20bodies%20and%20%E2%80%98curfewed%20nights%E2%80%99%20that%20were%20a%20recurrent%20theme%20of%20life%20in%20Kashmir%20during%20the%20heydays%20of%20insurgency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Call%20me%20Ishmael%20Tonight%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20poignant%20ghazal%20with%20allegedly%20blasphemous%20references%20in%20which%20Shahid%20tries%20to%20locate%20himself%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20religion%20and%20the%20conflict%20in%20Kashmir.%20The%20ghazal%20also%20refers%20to%20the%20destruction%20of%20some%20Hindu%20temples%20in%20the%20Valley%20when%20the%20conflict%20broke%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20poems%20were%20taught%20in%20the%20third%20semester%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Integrated%20Masters%20in%20English%E2%80%99%20programme%20at%20the%20CUS.%20Among%20other%20poets%20whose%20works%20are%20taught%20in%20the%20programme%20are%20the%20influential%20Urdu%20poet%2C%20Faiz%20Ahmad%20Faiz.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20syllabus%20for%20the%20five-year%20programme%20has%20not%20been%20updated%20yet%20and%20it%20is%20still%20accessible%20on%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20official%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20official%20explanation%20for%20the%20deletions%20and%20no%20order%20was%20passed%20in%20either%20of%20the%20instances.%20Professor%20Qayyum%20Hussain%2C%3Cbr%3E%5CnVice-Chancellor%20of%20CUS%2C%20could%20not%20be%20reached%20for%20his%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20former%20academic%20at%20the%20UOK%20said%20that%20Shahid%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdeeply%20secular%20poet%20whose%20heart%20was%20full%20of%20pain%20and%20anguish%20for%20both%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%E2%80%9D%20of%20Kashmir.%20%E2%80%9CAlthough%20his%20work%20touches%20on%20the%20themes%20of%20Kashmir%20conflict%2C%20the%20three%20poems%20(taught%20at%20UOK)%20have%20absolutely%20no%20political%20connotations%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fmaulana-azad-jammu-kashmir-ncert-dropped%5C%22%3ERevised%20NCERT%20Textbook%20Drops%20Statement%20That%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Accession%20Was%20Based%20on%20Promise%20of%20Autonomy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAgha%20Shahid%20Ali%3A%20%E2%80%98A%20voice%20like%20no%20other%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20widely%20read%20Kashmiri%20writers%20in%20English%2C%20Shahid%E2%80%99s%202001%20poetry%20collection%2C%20%3Cem%3ERooms%20are%20Never%20Finished%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0was%20the%20finalist%20for%20the%20National%20Book%20Award%2C%20the%20prestigious%20US%20literary%20prize%20whose%20winners%20include%20the%201949%20Nobel%20laureate%20William%20Faulkner%20and%20Pulitzer%20awardees%20Philip%20Roth%20and%20John%20Updike%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%20New%20Delhi%20and%20raised%20in%20the%20United%20States%20where%20he%20died%20of%20brain%20cancer%20in%202001%20aged%2052%2C%20Shahid%20was%20an%20alumnus%20of%20the%20UoK%20who%20had%20fulfilling%20teaching%20stints%20at%20the%20Delhi%20University%2C%20Princeton%20University%20and%20Hamilton%20College%20among%20other%20reputed%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EAmerican%20Alphabets%3A%2025%20Contemporary%20Poets%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20major%20anthology%20of%20American%20poetry%2C%20describes%20Shahid%20as%20one%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cextraordinary%20poets%20born%20since%20World%20War%20II.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHis%20voice%20was%20like%20none%20I%20had%20ever%20heard%20before%2C%20at%20once%20lyrical%20and%20fiercely%20disciplined%2C%20engaged%20and%20yet%20deeply%20inward%E2%80%A6the%20formalisation%20of%20the%20ghazal%20may%20well%20prove%20to%20be%20Shahid%E2%80%99s%20most%20important%20scholarly%20contribution%20to%20the%20canon%20of%20English%20poetry%2C%E2%80%9D%20author%20Amitav%20Ghosh%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Ghat%20of%20The%20Only%20World%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20essay%2C%20Ghosh%E2%80%99s%20tribute%20to%20his%20Kashmiri%20friend%2C%20which%20was%20published%20after%20Shahid%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Central%20Board%20of%20School%20Education%E2%80%99s%20Class%2011%20curriculum%20which%20is%20taught%20at%20more%20than%2027%2C000%20schools%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20tragedy%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20UOK%20official%2C%20who%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20be%20named%2C%20fearing%20reprisal%20from%20the%20authorities%2C%20%E2%80%9CStudents%20in%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%20read%20about%20Agha%20Shahid%20Ali%20but%20doing%20so%20in%20Kashmir%20is%20unacceptable%20now.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBasharat%20Peer%3A%20%E2%80%98Brutally%20honest%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeer%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ECurfewed%20Night%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20deeply%20personal%20and%20groundbreaking%20memoir%20of%20growing%20up%20in%20violence-ravaged%20Kashmir%2C%20received%20critical%20acclaim%20for%20drawing%20an%20unforgettable%20image%20of%20more%20than%20three%20decades%20of%20conflict%20in%20the%20Himalayan%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAuthor%20Khushwant%20Singh%20had%20called%20%3Cem%3ECurfewed%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ENight%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20%E2%80%9Cbrutally%20honest%20and%20deeply%20hurtful%E2%80%9D%20account%20while%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EGuardian%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20said%20it%20brings%20the%20%E2%80%9CKashmir%20conflict%20out%20of%20the%20realm%20of%20political%20rhetoric%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20and%20into%20the%20lives%20of%20Kashmiris.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20memoir%20took%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20English%20writing%20scene%20by%20a%20storm%20when%20it%20debuted%20in%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELondon-based%20Kashmiri%20writer%20and%20acclaimed%20novelist%20Mirza%20Waheed%20said%20that%20the%20decision%20to%20drop%20the%20two%20authors%20%E2%80%9Creinforces%E2%80%9D%20the%20idea%20that%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20is%20being%20run%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmost%20anti-intellectual%20and%20anti-thought%E2%80%9D%20administration.%20%E2%80%9CI%20suppose%20these%20days%20it%20must%20look%20good%20on%20a%20university%20administrators%E2%80%99s%20CV%20to%20say%20they%20removed%20a%20beautiful%20poet%20from%20their%20campus.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20Manoj%20Sinha%20is%20the%20Chancellor%20and%20de-facto%20head%20of%20the%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20terrible%20and%20sinister%20decision%2C%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20push%20to%20create%20%E2%80%98Naya%20(new)%20Kashmir%E2%80%99%20which%20means%20erasure%20of%20history%20%E2%80%93%20that%20we%20forget%20our%20history%2C%20our%20political%20and%20cultural%20heritage%2C%20our%20poets.%20It%20is%20a%20war%20on%20memory%2C%E2%80%9D%20Waheed%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWaheed%2C%20author%20of%20the%20novel%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Collaborator%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20said%20that%20the%20universities%20are%20a%20%E2%80%9Cplace%20of%20knowledge%2C%20thinking%20and%20critical%20engagement%20with%20literature%E2%80%9D%20which%20helps%20students%20in%20%E2%80%9Clocating%20themselves%20in%20the%20broader%20world.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CShahid%E2%80%99s%20poetry%20has%20been%20read%20in%20Kashmir%20and%20across%20the%20world%20for%20a%20long%20time%20and%20it%20will%20be%20read%20even%20more.%20Basharat%E2%80%99s%20memoir%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20books%20of%20the%20last%20few%20decades.%C2%A0You%20can%E2%80%99t%20erase%20Shahid%20from%20memory.%20You%20can%E2%80%99t%20make%3Cem%3E%20Curfewed%20Night%3C%2Fem%3E%20disappear%2C%E2%80%9D%20Waheed%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20over%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690103524000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F23143508%2FUntitled-design-6-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fkashmir-university-agha-shahid-ali-basharat-peer-dropped%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Univ