e%20attention%20of%20tech%20CEOs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bnolan%40insider.com%20(Beatrice%20Nolan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-ai-code-develop-software-guide-prompts-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bail%20Can't%20Be%20Refused%20As%20Indirect%20Punishment%3A%20Delhi%20Court%20In%20Bribery%20Case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20Delhi%20court%20has%20said%20bail%20cannot%20be%20refused%20as%20an%20indirect%20process%20of%20punishing%20an%20accused%20before%20he%20is%20convicted%20while%20releasing%20a%20man%20accused%20of%20taking%20a%20bribe%20of%20Rs%2012%20lakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpecial%20Judge%20Sunena%20Sharma%20granted%20bail%20to%20Rishi%20Raj%2C%20saying%20it%20is%20one%20of%20the%20basic%20principles%20of%20criminal%20jurisprudence%20that%20an%20accused%20is%20presumed%20to%20be%20innocent%20until%20proven%20guilty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20one%20of%20the%20basic%20principles%20of%20criminal%20jurisprudence%20that%20the%20accused%20is%20presumed%20to%20be%20innocent%20until%20proven%20guilty.%20Even%20assuming%20that%20the%20accused%20is%20prima%20facie%20guilty%20of%20an%20offence%2C%20bail%20cannot%20be%20refused%20in%20an%20indirect%20process%20of%20punishing%20the%20accused%20before%20he%20is%20convicted%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20said%20in%20the%20order%20passed%20on%20July%2017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20accused%20was%20in%20judicial%20custody%20for%20more%20than%20a%20month%20and%20the%20audio%20and%20video%20recordings%20of%20the%20alleged%20transaction%20were%20already%20in%20the%20possession%20of%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20further%20noted%20that%20the%20accused%20was%20a%20public%20servant%20and%20had%20no%20previous%20involvement%20in%20any%20such%20matter%2C%20though%20he%20was%20under%20suspension%20on%20account%20of%20this%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20such%20a%20scenario%2C%20the%20apprehension%20of%20the%20CBI%20that%20the%20accused%20may%20flee%20from%20justice%20or%20influence%20the%20witnesses%20is%20without%20any%20basis.%20Moreover%2C%20if%20the%20accused%20is%20found%20misusing%20bail%20by%20indulging%20in%20any%20such%20acts%2C%20the%20CBI%20may%20approach%20this%20court%20for%20cancellation%20of%20bail%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20granted%20the%20relief%20to%20the%20accused%20on%20a%20bail%20bond%20of%20Rs%2050%2C000%20with%20two%20sureties%20of%20a%20like%20amount%20and%20directed%20that%20the%20accused%20will%20not%20leave%20the%20country%20without%20the%20court's%20permission%20nor%20will%20he%20contact%20or%20influence%20the%20witnesses%20in%20any%20manner%20and%20will%20cooperate%20in%20the%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20was%20registered%20by%20the%20CBI%20on%20June%2012%20under%20sections%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Corruption%20Act%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20complaint%20from%20one%20Manoj%20Kumar%20Sheora%2C%20manager%20at%20the%20Gupta%20Multi-Speciality%20Hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20complainant%20had%20alleged%20that%20Raj%2C%20who%20was%20working%20as%20an%20enforcement%20officer%20in%20the%20Employees'%20Provident%20Fund%20Organisation%20(EPFO)%2C%20visited%20the%20hospital%20on%20April%2026%20and%20asked%20for%20documents%20related%20to%20records%20regarding%20the%20provident%20fund%20of%20the%20hospitals'%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20April%2027%2C%20the%20complainant%20visited%20the%20EPFO%20office%20and%20produced%20the%20relevant%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThereafter%2C%20the%20accused%20told%20the%20complainant%20about%20irregularities%20in%20the%20records%20and%20that%20a%20penalty%20of%20Rs%201.5%20crore%20would%20be%20imposed%20on%20account%20of%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20proposed%20to%20settle%20the%20matter%20without%20any%20penalty%20on%20the%20payment%20of%2020%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20amount%20as%20bribe%2C%20which%20he%20reduced%20to%20Rs%2012%20lakh%20on%20the%20request%20of%20the%20complainant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20complainant%20subsequently%20filed%20the%20complaint.%20A%20trap%20was%20laid%20and%20the%20accused%20was%20arrested%20while%20taking%20the%20bribe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20application%20sought%20bail%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20the%20accused%20had%20the%20responsibility%20to%20look%20after%20his%20aged%20parents%20and%20wife%2C%20who%20is%20seven%20months%20pregnant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20accused%20also%20claimed%20that%20no%20fruitful%20purpose%20would%20be%20served%20by%20further%20keeping%20him%20in%20custody%20as%20the%20investigation%20was%20almost%20complete%20and%20he%20was%20ready%20to%20join%20the%20probe%20as%20and%20when%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690102980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2Fcourt-generic_625x300_1527245477936.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbail-cant-be-refused-as-indirect-punishment-delhi-court-in-bribery-case-4233776%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Delhi%20court%20has%20said%20bail%20cannot%20be%20refused%20as%20an%20indirect%20process%20of%20punishing%20an%20accused%20before%20he%20is%20convicted%20while%20releasing%20a%20man%20accused%20of%20taking%20a%20bribe%20of%20Rs%2012%20lakh.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbail-cant-be-refused-as-indirect-punishment-delhi-court-in-bribery-case-4233776%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbail-cant-be-refused-as-indirect-punishment-delhi-court-in-bribery-case-4233776%2Famp%2F