20now%20used%20the%20Hubble%20telescope%20and%20discovered%20a%20swarm%20of%20boulders%20that%20were%20possibly%20shaken%20off%20the%20asteroid%20when%20NASA%20deliberately%20slammed%20the%20half-ton%20DART%20impactor%20spacecraft%20into%20Dimorphos%20at%20approximately%2014%2C000%20miles%20per%20hour%2C%20according%20to%20a%20NASA%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20images%20taken%20by%20the%20Hubble%20Space%20Telescope%20show%20that%20the%20collision%20also%20sent%2037%20boulders%20--%20ranging%20from%20one%20metre%20(three%20feet)%20to%20seven%20metres%20(22%20feet)%20across%20--%20floating%20into%20the%20cosmos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20represent%20around%20two%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20boulders%20that%20were%20already%20scattered%20across%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20loosely-held-together%20asteroid%2C%20scientists%20estimated%20in%20a%20new%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20finding%20suggests%20that%20possible%20future%20missions%20to%20divert%20life-threatening%20asteroids%20heading%20towards%20Earth%20could%20also%20spray%20off%20boulders%20in%20our%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20these%20particular%20rocks%20do%20not%20pose%20any%20threat%20to%20Earth%20--%20indeed%20they%20have%20barely%20gone%20anywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20drifting%20away%20from%20Dimorphos%20at%20around%20a%20kilometre%20(half%20a%20mile)%20per%20hour%20--%20roughly%20the%20speed%20a%20giant%20tortoise%20walks%2C%20Hubble%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20boulders%20are%20moving%20so%20slowly%20that%20the%20European%20Space%20Agency's%20Hera%20mission%20--%20which%20is%20due%20to%20arrive%20at%20the%20asteroid%20in%20late%202026%20to%20inspect%20the%20damage%20--%20will%20even%20be%20able%20to%20take%20a%20look%20at%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20boulder%20cloud%20will%20still%20be%20dispersing%20when%20Hera%20arrives%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20David%20Jewitt%2C%20a%20planetary%20scientist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%20at%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20new%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20a%20very%20slowly%20expanding%20swarm%20of%20bees%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bspectacular%20observation%26quot%3B%20by%20Hubble%20%26quot%3Btells%20us%20for%20the%20first%20time%20what%20happens%20when%20you%20hit%20an%20asteroid%20and%20see%20material%20coming%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20boulders%20are%20some%20of%20the%20faintest%20things%20ever%20imaged%20inside%20our%20solar%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dispersal%20of%20the%20boulders%20indicates%20that%20DART%20left%20a%20crater%20roughly%2050%20metres%20(160%20feet)%20wide%20on%20Dimorphos%2C%20according%20to%20Jewitt.%20The%20whole%20asteroid%20is%20170%20metres%20across.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20plan%20to%20continue%20following%20the%20boulders%20to%20work%20out%20their%20trajectory%20and%20determine%20how%20exactly%20they%20launched%20off%20the%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20was%20published%20in%20the%20Astrophysical%20Journal%20Letters.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690093560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2F6a22hapg_nasas-hubble-space-telescope_625x300_23_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasas-asteroid-smashing-space-debris-spotted-by-hubble-telescope-4233471%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22New%20images%20taken%20by%20the%20Hubble%20Space%20Telescope%20show%20that%20the%20collision%20also%20sent%2037%20boulders%20--%20ranging%20from%20one%20metre%20to%20seven%20metres%20across.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasas-asteroid-smashing-space-debris-spotted-by-hubble-telescope-4233471%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasas-asteroid-smashing-space-debris-