rities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20last%20four%20years%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20witnessed%20severe%20escalating%20attacks%20on%20religious%20minorities%20under%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%E2%80%A6%20And%20yet%20we%20know%20our%20own%20US%20State%20Department%20has%20yet%20to%20designate%20India%20as%20a%20Country%20of%20Particular%20Concern%20under%20US%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%2C%20as%20per%20a%20press%20release%20on%20the%20briefing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20bi-partisan%20US%20state-department%20funded%20US%20Commission%20on%20International%20Religious%20Freedom%20(USCIRF)%20has%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fuscirf-country-of-particular-concern-fourth-time%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erecommended%20for%20four%20consecutive%20years%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20India%20should%20be%20designated%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98Country%20of%20Particular%20Concern%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20State%20department.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETill%20now%2C%20the%20US%20state%20department%20has%20refused%20to%20take%20any%20such%20action.%20The%20Indian%20government%20has%20accused%20USCIRF%20of%20reiterating%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-lashes-out-uscirf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebiased%20and%20motivated%20comments%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20about%20the%20country%20in%20its%20annual%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20briefing%2C%20USCIRF%20Commissioner%20David%20Curry%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20Commission%20had%20urged%20the%20Biden%20administration%20to%20raise%20religious%20freedom%20concerns%20during%20the%20Indian%20PM%E2%80%99s%20state%20visit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CReligious%20freedom%20was%20mentioned%20briefly%20during%20the%20visit%20but%20was%20certainly%20not%20a%20focal%2