y%20transplant%20or%20dialysis%2C%20which%20would%20have%20required%20her%20to%20go%20to%20the%20hospital%20thrice%20a%20week.%20After%20three%20months%20of%20taking%20medication%2C%20the%20kidney%20failure%20was%20reversed%2C%20and%20she%20felt%20like%20she%20had%20been%20given%20another%20life.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Three%20Claims%20of%20Government%20Economists%20About%20Jobs%20Put%20to%20the%20Test%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F23103952%2F3158023774_54f2900169_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EI%20will%20discuss%20three%20claims%20made%20by%20government%20economists%2C%20basing%20my%20analysis%20on%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20own%20National%20Survey%20Organization%E2%80%99s%20(NSO)%20data%2C%20the%20Labour%20Force%20Surveys.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFirst%20claim%3A%20there%20has%20been%20%E2%80%98jobful%20growth%E2%80%99!%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20claimed%20that%20there%20was%20a%2058%20million%20increase%20in%20jobs%20between%20calendar%20years%202019%20and%202022%2C%20the%20highest%20in%20Indian%20history%20over%20three%20years.%20The%20same%20authors%20also%20claim%2C%20bizarrely%2C%20that%20employment%20growth%20from%202004-5%20to%202011-12%20(India%E2%80%99s%20highest%20ever%20GDP%20growth%20period)%20during%20the%20United%20Progressive%20Alliance%20years%20was%20very%20weak%20%E2%80%93%20just%2013.3%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20claims%20ignore%20that%20most%20of%20the%2058%20million%20%E2%80%98jobs%E2%80%99%20claim%20rests%20upon%20the%20increase%20in%20%E2%80%98employment%E2%80%99%20in%20agriculture%20during%20Covid.%20In%202019%2C%20there%20were%20188%20mn%20workers%20in%20agriculture%3B%20in%20mid-2020%2C%20reverse%20migration%20raised%20it%20by%2045%20million.%20For%20anyone%20believing%20that%20in%202021%2C%20the%20migration%20had%20reversed%20back%20to%20the%20cities%20and%20away%20from%20agriculture%2C%20the%20NSO%20data%20throws%20up%20a%20surprise%3A%20in%202021%2C%207%20mn%20additional%20people%20were%20working%20in%20agriculture%20compared%20to%202020.%20Between%202004-5%20and%202011-12%2C%2037%20million%20workers%20exited%20agriculture%2C%20a%20good%20development%2C%20as%20non-farm%20job%20growth%20rose%20sharply%20to%207.5%20mn%20per%20annum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%C2%A0%20as%20non-farm%20job%20growth%20had%20fallen%20post-2013%20(to%20only%202.9%20mn%20pa%20till%202019)%2C%20the%20rate%20of%20exit%20from%20agriculture%20also%20fell.%20GDP%20growth%20fell%20sharply%20from%202016%20for%20each%20quarter%20until%20Covid%20broke.%20India%E2%80%99s%20open%20unemployment%20rate%20in%202017-18%20had%20risen%20to%20a%2045-year%20high.%20And%20then%20the%20ill-planned%20national%20lockdown%20caused%20massive%20reverse%20migration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgriculture%20is%20labour%20surplus%2C%20and%20rising%20employment%20in%20it%20lowers%20productivity%20and%20real%20incomes%20among%20those%20dependent%20on%20agriculture.%20Worse%2C%20it%20is%20the%20opposite%20of%20the%20structural%20change%20sought%20%E2%80%95%20a%20fall%20in%20the%20share%20of%20agriculture%20in%20GDP%20and%20a%20rise%20in%20non-farm%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorse%20still%2C%20most%20of%20this%20so-called%20increase%20in%20%E2%80%98jobs%E2%80%99%20in%20agriculture%20since%202019%20is%20in%20%E2%80%98unpaid%20family%20labour%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20form%20of%20self-employment%20where%20women%2C%20youth%20and%20children%20join%20other%20family%20members%20to%20appear%20%E2%80%98employed%E2%80%99.%20In%20ILO%E2%80%99s%20definition%2C%20followed%20by%2092%20other%20countries%20but%20not%20India%2C%20for%20no%20reason%20other%20than%20the%20NSO%E2%80%99s%20cussedness%20to%20not%20adopt%20definitions%20that%20ILO%20members%2C%20under%20India%E2%80%99s%20chairmanship%20in%202013%20of%20the%2019%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%C2%A0International%20Conference%20of%20Labour%20Statisticians%2C%20had%20agreed%20upon.%20The%20Centre%20for%20Monitoring%20the%20Indian%20Economy%2C%20generating%20monthly%20data%20on%20employment%20since%202016%2C%20follows%20the%20ILO%20definition%2C%20and%20hence%20has%20shown%20consistent%20increases%20in%20unemployment%2C%20and%20reductions%20in%20labour%20force%20and%20workforce%20participation%20rates%20in%20India%20since%202016%2C%20while%20NSO%20shows%20the%20opposite%2C%20despite%20falling%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20second%20claim%3A%20real%20wages%20have%20increased%20recently!%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFigure%201%3A%20Real%20Wages%20(in%20Rs.%20at%202011%20price)%20by%20sector%20and%20type%20of%20employment%2C%202018-2022%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPanel%20A%3A%20Agriculture%20%26amp%3B%20Allied%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20cellspacing%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20cellpadding%3D%5C%220%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F0a103129-2325-491e-8a57-536b90df7796%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F0a103129-2325-491e-8a57-536b90df7796%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1690173811212000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw2AjSF7YdOexhMwbteqS9_O%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fci3.googleusercontent.com%2Fproxy%2FzTCO3YxSVpxXL235GsjmSSiOPCSsFR6o2ov_54pTSKHuByBnoW8k27Axc3AYTFJ5peAL2LJ-C4qgP55Peqd8mpExxsNCpE6YRJlTGzalsxWqTGyDa4sQPnnYynCRPZGbkTxLmeNuXs3AvZ6dQnbdo44Ze