f%20Bezos%20is%20playing%20an%20increasingly%20active%20role%20in%20operations%20at%20The%20Post%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20Amazon%20founder%20and%20ex-chief%20executive%20made%20an%20unusual%20visit%20to%20the%20newsroom%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBezos%20has%20sought%20to%20make%20The%20Post%20an%20international%20force%20and%20has%20encouraged%20digital%20experimentation.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20Amazon%20chief%20executive%20and%20president%20Jeff%20Bezos%20has%20become%20increasingly%20involved%20in%20the%20operations%20of%20The%20Washington%20Post%2C%20the%20venerable%20newspaper%20that%20he%20purchased%20for%20%24250%20million%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F07%2F22%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia%2Fjeff-bezos-washington-post.html%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20past%20years%2C%20representatives%20of%20Bezos%20kept%20close%20tabs%20on%20the%20budget%2C%20but%20Bezos%20has%20recently%20taken%20a%20more%20active%20approach%20as%20the%20publication%20has%20encountered%20economic%20headwinds%20and%20internal%20dissent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20early%202021%2C%20The%20Post%20boasted%203%20million%20digital%20subscribers%2C%20fueled%20by%20the%20lightning-speed%20news%20cycles%20of%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20and%20had%20more%20than%201%2C000%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20up%20from%20about%20580%20staffers%20before%20Bezos'%20investment%20in%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20digital%20subscriptions%20now%20sit%20at%202.5%20million%2C%20and%20the%20newspaper%20has%20stumbled%20in%20boosting%20that%20figure%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Times%20report%20noted%20that%20The%20Post%20was%20set%20to%20lose%20%24100%20million%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20two%20individuals%20with%20knowledge%20of%20The%20Post's%20financial%20situation%20who%20spoke%20to%20the%20newspaper.%20Two%20other%20individuals%20also%20told%20The%20Times%20that%20The%20Post%20was%20projected%20to%20miss%20its%20advertising%20revenue%20estimates%20for%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatty%20Stonesifer%2C%20the%20interim%20chief%20executive%20for%20The%20Post%2C%20told%20The%20Times%20that%20Bezos%20was%20thrilled%20with%20%26quot%3Bevery%20dollar%20invested%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20company.%20And%20an%20individual%20with%20knowledge%20of%20Bezos'%20vision%20for%20The%20Post%20said%20that%202023%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Byear%20for%20investment%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20very%20enthusiastic%20about%20what%20we%20can%20do%20here%20at%20The%20Washington%20Post%20in%20the%20decade%20ahead%2C%26quot%3B%20Stonesifer%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BJeff's%20second%20decade%20of%20ownership%20of%20The%20Post%20should%20be%20even%20more%20exciting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Bezos%20bought%20The%20Post%20in%202013%2C%20it%20was%20the%20end%20of%20an%20era%20for%20the%20newspaper%2C%20which%20for%20generations%20had%20been%20run%20by%20the%20Graham%20family%2C%20whose%20stewardship%20saw%20the%20paper%20ascend%20to%20monumental%20heights%20with%20its%20Watergate%20and%20Pentagon%20Papers%20coverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBezos%20encouraged%20digital%20experimentation%20when%20he%20first%20bought%20the%20newspaper%2C%20angling%20to%20make%20The%20Post%20into%20an%20international%20powerhouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Bezos'%20initial%20purchase%20of%20The%20Post%2C%20his%20influence%20was%20less%20visible%20in%20the%20newsroom%2C%20according%20to%20two%20individuals%20who%20spoke%20with%20The%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20morale%20cratered%2C%20editor%20Sally%20Buzbee%20%E2%80%94%20whom%20Bezos%20had%20helped%20select%20to%20succeed%20veteran%20editor%20Marty%20Baron%20%E2%80%94%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20Amazon%20founder%20to%20discuss%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20Bezos%20made%20an%20unusual%20visit%20to%20the%20newsroom%2C%20attending%20a%20morning%20meeting%20and%20later%20meeting%20with%20several%20journalists%20at%20the%20paper.%20The%20journalists%20reportedly%20spoke%20with%20Bezos%20about%20some%20larger%20newsroom%20issues%20with%20Fred%20Ryan%20%E2%80%94%20the%20newspaper's%20publisher%20%E2%80%94%20who%20in%20June%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fpr%2F2023%2F06%2F12%2Ffred-ryan-publisher-ceo-announces-decision-step-down-washington-post-lead-new-civility-initiative%2F%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20would%20step%20down%20from%20his%20position%20later%20in%20the%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBezos%20has%20continued%20to%20look%20ahead%20as%20he%20seeks%20to%20put%20his%20imprint%20on%20the%20newspaper's%20vision.%20He%20is%20mulling%20over%20an%20experimental%20project%20for%20the%20opinion%20section%2C%20and%20an%20overhaul%20of%20the%20paper's%20Style%20section%20is%20expected%20later%20in%20the%20year%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESally%20Quinn%2C%20a%20longtime%20journalist%20at%20the%20newspaper%20and%20the%20widow%20of%20Post%20legend%20Ben%20Bradlee%2C%20told%20The%20Times%20that%20she%20had%20renewed%20optimism%20for%20the%20newsroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20sense%20of%20hope%2C%20which%20we%20haven't%20had%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-washington-post-operations-newspaper-digital-subscriptions-amazon-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690056394000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64bc3504bea34400195f4450%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-washington-post-operations-newspaper-digital-subscriptions-amazon-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20are%20now%202.5%20million%20digital%20Post%20subscribers%2C%20down%20from%203%20million%20in%202020%2C%20and%20the%20paper%20has%20stumbled%20in%20boosting%20that%20figure%2C%20per%20The%20Times.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(John%20L.%20Dorman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A112%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-washington-post-operations-newspaper-digital-subscriptions-amazon-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Vaping%20was%20marketed%20as%20an%20avenue%20to%20quit%20smoking%20cigarettes.%20But%20some%20smokers%20are%20now%20just%20doing%20both%2C%20CDC%20study%20finds.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221885%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Man%20vaping.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64bc318d5adc5f0019521979%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20CDC%20is%20warning%20of%20negative%20health%20effects%20for%20people%20who%20smoke%20both%20vapes%20and%20cigarettes.%3Cp%3Edanchooalex%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20new%20CDC%20study%20found%20that%20some%20people%20have%20taken%20to%20smoking%20both%20cigarettes%20and%20vapes.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EVapes%20were%20previously%20pitched%20as%20a%20way%20to%20switch%20or%20quit%20smoking%20cigarettes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPeople%20who%20smoke%20both%20risk%20more%20%26quot%3Bexposure%20to%20toxins%20and%20worse%20respiratory%20outcomes%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CDC%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20would%20you%20%26quot%3Bpick%20your%20poison%26quot%3B%20when%20you%20can%20enjoy%20both%3F%20Poor%20health%20outcomes.%20That's%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20is%20now%20warning%20people%20who%20smoke%20both%20vapes%20and%20cigarettes%20about%20the%20negative%20health%20effects.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDual%20use%20of%20tobacco%20products%20is%20a%20health%20concern%20because%20it%20may%20result%20in%20greater%20exposure%20to%20toxins%20and%20worse%20respiratory%20outcomes%20than%20using%20either%20product%20alone%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CDC%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnchs%2Fdata%2Fdatabriefs%2Fdb475.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enewly%20released%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20e-cigarette%20(or%20vape)%20use%20in%20adults%20in%202021.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUse%20of%20both%20products%20was%20highest%20in%20adults%20aged%2018%20to%2044%2C%20the%20CDC%20found.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVapes%20have%20previously%20been%20marketed%20as%20a%20way%20to%20quit%20smoking%20cigarettes.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2019%2F09%2F05%2Fjuul-accused-of-illegally-advertising-vaping-as-a-way-to-quit-smoking.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epast%20campaign%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20Juul%2C%20an%20e-cigarette%20company%20that%20was%20federally%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjuul-labs-vape-agrees-pay-438-million-probe-teen-marketing-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestigated%20for%20its%20marketing%20to%20young%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20encouraged%20people%20to%20%26quot%3Bmake%20the%20switch%26quot%3B%20to%20e-cigarettes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20seems%20some%20of%20those%20people%20just%20ended%20up%20smoking%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Food%20and%20Drug%20Administration%20has%20not%20found%20any%20e-cigarette%20to%20be%20safe%20and%20effective%20in%20helping%20smokers%20quit.%20The%20fact%20is%2C%20e-cigarettes%20are%20tobacco%20products%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20reads%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lung.org%2Fquit-smoking%2Fe-cigarettes-vaping%2Fquit-dont-switch%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20American%20Lung%20Association%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20group.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20all%20American%20adults%2C%20the%20CDC%20study%20found%20that%2010.2%25%20smoked%20only%20cigarettes%2C%203.2%25%20smoked%20only%20e-cigarettes%2C%20and%201.3%25%20smoked%20both.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EE-cigarette%20use%20was%20greatest%20in%20young%20adults%20aged%2018%20to%2024%2C%20where%2011%25%20reported%20using%20them.%20Most%20adults%20in%20that%20age%20category%20reported%20that%20they%20never%20smoked%20cigarettes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDespite%20this%2C%20the%20percentage%20of%20adults%20aged%2018-24%20who%20were%20dual%20users%20of%20e-cigarettes%20and%20cigarettes%20was%20similar%20to%20the%20percentage%20among%20adults%20aged%2025-44%20(1.8%25%20compared%20with%202.0%25)%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study%20found.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20adults%20aged%2045%20and%20over%20largely%20preferred%20cigarettes%20only%2C%20reporting%20the%20lowest%20percentages%20of%20e-cigarette%20use%20or%20dual%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeople-smoking-both-vapes-cigarettes-cdc-study-finds-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690056025000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64bc318d5adc5f0019521979%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeople-smoking-both-vapes-cigarettes-cdc-study-finds-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20CDC%20is%20warning%20people%20who%20choose%20to%20smoke%20both%20cigarettes%20and%20vapes%20that%20they%20risk%20%26quot%3Bgreater%20exposure%20to%20toxins%20and%20worse%20respiratory%20outcomes.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kbalevic%40insider.com%20(Katie%20Balevic)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A26%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeople-smoking-both-vapes-cigarettes-cdc-study-finds-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20brewery%20is%20making%20beer%20with%