0that%20about%2030%25%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20covering%20more%20than%2067%2C000%20square%20miles%2C%20had%20been%20subject%20to%20heavy%20fighting%20and%20would%20require%20thorough%20clearance%20operations.%20The%20report%20also%20detailed%20the%20lengths%20taken%20by%20Russian%20forces%20to%20make%20vast%20expanses%20of%20Ukrainian%20farmland%20either%20too%20difficult%20to%20navigate%20or%20effectively%20unusable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BTo%20date%2C%20the%20Kharkiv%20and%20Kherson%20oblasts%20remain%20the%20most%20contaminated%20regions%20of%20all%20the%20liberated%20territories%2C%20as%20Russian%20forces%20had%20been%20present%20there%20for%20a%20longer%20period%20of%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20nature%20of%20the%20demining%20challenge%20is%20different%20to%20the%20pre-Feb%202022%20situation%3A%20First%2C%20fighting%20has%20been%20heavier%20and%20longer%20in%20duration%3B%20second%2C%20a%20far%20greater%20range%20of%20explosive%20ordnance%20has%20been%20deployed%2C%20and%2C%20finally%2C%20the%20area%20of%20potentially%20contaminated%20territory%20is%2010%20times%20greater.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BRussian%20troops%20are%20infamously%20creative%20in%20leaving%20mine%20traps%3A%20They%20plant%20victim-activated%20devices%20on%20animals%2C%20dead%20bodies%2C%20as%20well%20as%20double%20and%20even%20triple%20booby%20traps%20on%20roads%2C%20fields%2C%20and%20forests%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20continued.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20been%20reported%20that%20the%20Russians%20have%20also%20deliberately%20targeted%20farming%20areas%20and%20agricultural%20land%20for%20contamination%20in%20order%20to%20deny%20its%20use%20for%20future%20economic%20activity%20in%20Ukraine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22d