76788.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22AP%3A%20Political%20Parties%20Want%20Voter%20Privacy%20Protected%20%E2%80%93%20As%20Long%20as%20They%20Are%20Not%20in%20Power%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F22171517%2Fvoter-id.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20YSR%20Congress%20(YSRC)%20Party%20that%20first%20demanded%20the%20protection%20of%20voters%E2%80%99%20privacy%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20during%20the%202019%20elections.%20The%20demand%20was%20made%20in%20the%20backdrop%20of%20Telugu%20Desam%20Party%20(TDP)%20members%20getting%20caught%20with%20the%20%3Cem%3ESeva%20Mitra%3C%2Fem%3E%20app%2C%20containing%20colour%20photos%20and%20360-degree%20profiles%20of%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20political%20tides%20have%20changed.%20Now%2C%20the%20Jana%20Sena%20Party%20is%20demanding%20%E2%80%9CMy%20Data%2C%20My%20Right%E2%80%9D%2C%20protesting%20against%20the%20Jagan%20Mohan%20Reddy%20government%E2%80%99s%20village%20volunteers%20collecting%20personal%20data.%20The%20TDP%2C%20too%2C%20has%20joined%20in%2C%20demanding%20an%20end%20to%20360-degree%20profiling.%20Then%20what%20is%20the%20problem%20with%20the%20voters%E2%80%99%20privacy%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20TDP%20government%20from%202014%20to%202019%20that%20pioneered%20360-degree%20profiling%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERetired%20bureaucrat%20J.%20Satyanarayana%2C%20who%20was%20the%20Unique%20Identification%20Authority%20of%20India%20(UIDAI)%20chairman%20and%20IT%20advisor%20to%20the%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20government%2C%20championed%20the%20cause%20of%20real-time%20governance%20and%20360-degree%20profiling%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20was%20the%20second%20state%20to%20do%20the%20profiling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETelangana%20had%20already%20started%20implementing%20it%20before%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20did%20with%20its%20%3Cem%3ESamagra%20Kutumba%20%3C%2Fem%3ESurvey%20and%20Integrated%20People%20Information%20Hub.%20Both%20Telangana%20and%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20were%20the%20ground%20zero%20of%20these%20new%20experiments%20of%20pushing%20Aadhaar-based%20360-degree%20profiling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImported%20model%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20model%20of%20governance%20and%20push%20for%20Aadhaar%20is%20not%20native%20to%20India.%20It%20was%20primarily%20experimented%20in%20Estonia%20in%20Europe%20and%20later%20suggested%20to%20our%20bureaucrats%20to%20be%20adopted.%20The%20early%20experiment%20of%20the%20AP%20Smart%20Card%20project%20in%202006%20under%20Y.S.%20Rajasekhara%20Reddy%20was%20the%20precursor%20to%20the%20Aadhaar%20project%2C%20even%20before%20Nandan%20Nilekani%20adopted%20it%20to%20be%20enforced%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnited%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20was%20the%20laboratory%20to%20experiment%20with%20the%20implementation%20of%20new%20governance%20models%20and%20technologies%20because%20of%20globalisation%20and%20its%20IT%20sector%E2%80%99s%20place%20in%20global%20trade.%20The%20bureaucracy%20was%20open%20to%20experimenting%20with%20anything%20new%20in%20the%20population%20to%20be%20ahead%20in%20global%20supply%20chains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20many%20problems%20with%20Aadhaar-based%20360-degree%20profiling%20and%20there%20has%20been%20large-scale%20opposition%20to%20it%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20recognising%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Aadhaar%20project%20itself%20was%20heavily%20restricted%20by%20the%20court%2C%20saying%20it%20should%20be%20used%20only%20for%20welfare.%20Yet%2C%20the%20government%20passed%20new%20laws%20and%20rules%20to%20push%20it%2C%20disregarding%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20nature%20of%20the%20Aadhaar%20project%20and%20360-degree%20profiling%20allows%20the%20government%20to%20track%20citizens%20from%20birth%20to%20death.%20This%20was%20necessary%20for%20the%20government%20in%20a%20post-26%2F11%20India%2C%20where%20the%20government%20wanted%20to%20know%20everyone%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20threat%20to%20civil%20liberties%20was%20always%20on%20since%20this%20information%20can%20be%20misused%2C%20affecting%20electoral%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21211445%2FAadhaar-1200x560-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21211445%2FAadhaar-1200x560-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21211445%2FAadhaar-1200x560-1-300x140.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21211445%2FAadhaar-1200x560-1-1024x478.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664450%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3Eillustration%3A%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20big%20player%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Aadhaar-Voter%20ID%20linking%20experiments%20in%20Telangana%20and%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20resulted%20in%20denying%20lakhs%20of%20voters%20the%20right%20to%20franchise%20in%20the%202018%20assembly%20elections%20in%20Telangana.%20It%20also%20resulted%20in%20Aadhaar%20profiles%20being%20used%20for%20electioneering%20at%20large.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20these%20issues%20were%20ignored%20%E2%80%93%20and%20continue%20to%20be%20ignored%20and%20unacknowledged%20%E2%80%93%20because%20the%20Indian%20IT%20sector%20pushes%20towards%20a%20data%20economy.%20Everything%20from%20Aadhaar%2C%20UPI%2C%20Digital%20Locker%2C%20and%20CoWIN%20are%20being%20exported%20to%20other%20countries%20just%20the%20way%20they%20have%20been%20imported%20into%20India%20from%20Estonia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWelfare%20was%20always%20used%20as%20an%20excuse%20to%20push%20technologies%20that%20the%20Indian%20IT%20sector%20could%20use%20to%20create%20a%20domestic%20IT%20economy.%20Even%20today%2C%20the%20biggest%20opposition%20to%20the%20Privacy%20and%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20is%20from%20the%20Indian%20IT%20sector%2C%20not%20politicians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20every%20level%20of%20the%20Aadhaar%20litigation%2C%20it%20was%20not%20only%20the%20government%20but%20the%20Indian%20IT%20sector%20also%20opposed%20a%20pushback.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20strict%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20will%20address%20issues%20of%20government%20data%20collection%20and%20how%20data%20is%20affecting%20elections%20and%20electoral%20politics.%20But%20these%20have%20been%20ignored%20by%20allowing%20the%20government%20to%20have%20exceptions%20to%20collect%20as%20much%20data%20as%20it%20wants%20to%20implement%20the%20rule%20of%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20present%20draft%20of%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202022%2C%20is%20not%20good%20enough%20to%20protect%20the%20citizens%E2%80%99%20rights%20and%20it%20is%20just%20a%20rubber%20stamp%20on%20all%20government%20projects.%20A%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20respecting%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20on%20Aadhaar%20and%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20privacy%20would%20not%20allow%20360-degree%20profiling.%20The%20draft%20Bill%20envisages%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20political%20opposition%20seen%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20is%20necessary%20to%20make%20people%20understand%20the%20dangers%20of%20information%20and%20with%20successive%20pushbacks%2C%20the%20people%20may%20realise%20the%20larger%20problem%20irrespective%20of%20whose%20politics%20prevail.%20But%20notwithstanding%20the%20opposition%20to%20these%20systems%2C%20as%20long%20as%20they%20are%20not%20opposed%20nationally%2C%20they%20will%20remain%20the%20same%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWanted%3A%20Global%20demand%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20TDP%E2%80%99s%20plan%20to%20draw%20the%20attention%20of%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20to%20the%20issue%20of%20360-degree%20profiling%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20is%20useless%20when%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20(MHA)%20itself%20wants%20360-degree%20profiling%20databases%20like%20NATGRID%2C%20CCTNS%2C%20and%20ICJS%20for%20surveilling%20the%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndians%20already%20have%20a%20fundamental%20right%20to%20privacy%2C%20but%20who%20will%20implement%20it%20when%20the%20governments%20at%20both%20the%20Centre%20and%20state%20support%20Aadhaar%3F%20No%20court%20can%20implement%20its%20order%20or%20get%20these%20systems%20changed%20unless%20there%20is%20a%20change%20in%20the%20technical%20architecture%20of%20the%20Aadhaar%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20moment%2C%20this%20will%20happen%20only%20if%20there%20is%20a%20global%20demand%20from%20countries%20that%20want%20to%20buy%20Aadhaar%2C%20to%20change%20its%20code%20and%20architecture%20to%20respect%20individual%20privacy.%20No%20matter%20how%20much%20Indians%20demand%20privacy%2C%20the%20current%20technical%20and%20governance%20setup%20does%20not%20allow%20any%20political%20party%20to%20change%20what%20is%20already%20built.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20MHA%20is%20introducing%20a%20Bill%20for%20amending%20the%20Registration%20of%20Births%20and%20Deaths%20Act%2C%201969%2C%20in%20the%20ongoing%20Parliament%20session.%20The%20Bill%20seeks%20to%20link%20all%20major%20government%20databases%20at%20the%20Centre%20and%20state%20to%20build%20the%20National%20Population%20Register%20using%20Aadhaar%20as%20a%20unique%20ID.%20The%20Bill%20puts%20into%20law%20the%20idea%20of%20360-degree%20profiling%20and%20allows%20the%20MHA%20to%20track%20citizens%20from%20birth%20to%20death%2C%20something%20that%20has%20been%20widely%20experimented%20with%20and%20accepted%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20amount%20of%20opposition%20will%20change%20the%20360-degree%20profiling%20even%20though%20everyone%20knows%20it%20is%20bad.%20Every%20political%20party%20in%20power%20will%20continue%20to%20push%20it%20and%20oppose%20it%20when%20in%20Opposition.%20This%20is%20how%20the%20Indian%20state%20functions%3A%20Aadhaar%20is%20now%20part%20of%20statecraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20published%20under%20Creative%20Commons%20Attribution%E2%80%93No%20Derivatives%204.0%20International%20(CC%20BY-ND%204.0).%20Read%20the%20original%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthesouthfirst.com%2Fopinion%2Fevery-political-party-in-andhra-pradesh-wants-voters-privacy-protected-but-why-cant-they-have-it%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690026607000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F22171517%2Fvoter-id.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fandhra-pradesh-voter-privacy-aadhaar%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22No%20matter%20how%20much%20privacy%20Indians%20demand%2C%20the%20current%20technical%20and%20governance%20setup%20does%20not%20allow%20any%20political%20party%20to%20change%20what%20is%20already%20built.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fandhra-pradesh-voter-privacy-aadhaar%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Original%20%E2%80%98Oppenheimer%E2%80%99%3A%20How%20the%20BBC%20Brought%20the%20Father%20of%20the%20Atom%20Bomb%20to%20Life%20Long%20Before%20Christopher%20Nolan%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690026072000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FSam-Waterston-Oppenheimer-BBC.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235677307%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Decades%20before%20Christopher%20Nolan%20set%20his%20si